@startuml data_ingestion_sequence
title Provider Data Ingestion Flow - Loading HouseholdMeasurement data via Kong
hide footbox

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor          #555555
    ActorBorderColor    #555555
    LifeLineBorderColor #999999
    LifeLineBackgroundColor #EEEEEE
    ParticipantBorderColor #555555
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #B3D9FF
    NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
    NoteBorderColor     #999999
}

actor "Provider Application\n(EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA)\norion_ld_loading_script_kong.py" as Provider
participant "Kong API Gateway\n(kong-standalone:8000)" as Kong
participant "iSHARE Satellite\n(ishare-satellite:8080)" as Satellite
participant "Orion-LD\n(fiware-orion-ld:1026)" as Orion

== Step 1: Provider reads CSV data ==

Provider -> Provider : pd.read_csv('2022-07.csv')\nRead HouseholdMeasurement rows\nfrom Plegma dataset

== Step 2: For each row, create iSHARE JWT ==

loop For each row in CSV

    Provider -> Provider : get_ishare_token():\nbuild JWT with\n• iss=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA\n• sub=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA\n• aud=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA\n• x5c=[client.pem, ca.pem]\n• exp=now+30s\nsign with client.key (RS256)

    note right of Provider
    New token per row because
    iSHARE JWTs expire in 30 seconds
    end note

    == Step 3: Build NGSI-LD entity ==

    Provider -> Provider : Build NGSI-LD entity:\n{\n  id: urn:ngsi-ld:HouseholdMeasurement:House1:<timestamp>,\n  type: HouseholdMeasurement,\n  aggregateActivePower: {type: Property, value: ...},\n  aggregateVoltage: {type: Property, value: ...},\n  appliancePower: {type: Property, value: {...}},\n  @context: smart-data-models/Energy/context.jsonld\n}

    == Step 4: POST entity to Kong ==

    Provider -> Kong : POST /ngsi-ld/v1/entities\nContent-Type: application/ld+json\nAuthorization: Bearer <iSHARE JWT>\nBody: <NGSI-LD entity JSON>

    activate Kong

    == Step 5: Kong validates the JWT ==

    Kong -> Kong : ngsi-ishare-policies plugin:\nparse JWT, extract x5c chain

    Kong -> Satellite : GET /token\n(Kong authenticates as EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA)
    activate Satellite
    Satellite --> Kong : access_token
    deactivate Satellite

    Kong -> Satellite : GET /trusted_list\nAuthorization: Bearer <access_token>
    activate Satellite
    Satellite --> Kong : List of trusted CA fingerprints
    deactivate Satellite

    Kong -> Kong : Verify JWT signature\nagainst trusted CA list: VALID ✓\niss=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA == local authority\n→ no delegation needed

    == Step 6: Kong forwards POST to Orion-LD ==

    Kong -> Orion : POST /ngsi-ld/v1/entities\nContent-Type: application/ld+json\nBody: <NGSI-LD entity JSON>
    activate Orion
    Orion -> Orion : Validate NGSI-LD entity\nStore in MongoDB
    Orion --> Kong : 201 Created
    deactivate Orion

    Kong --> Provider : 201 Created
    deactivate Kong

    Provider -> Provider : print("Row ingested successfully via Kong")

end

note over Provider, Orion
After ingestion, all HouseholdMeasurement entities
are stored in Orion-LD and accessible via Kong
to authorized participants (Provider and Consumer).
end note

@enduml
